-- Koks Worker Dies Building Russian Coal Mine After Wall Collapses
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-06-14T08:39:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/koks-worker-dies-building-russian-coal-mine-after-wall-collapses.html
OAO Koks, a Russian coal and pig-
iron producer, said a worker building its Butovskaya project in
Siberia’s Kemerovo region died after a mine wall collapsed.  The accident won’t affect plans to open the mine in 2013,
Sergey Frolov, a spokesman for the company, said today by phone  To contact the reporter on this story:
